=== 生態問題 ===
「一带一路」倡議引起了環保組織的關注。 世界自然基金會和匯豐銀行的一份聯合報告認為，「一带一路」倡議為可持續發展帶來了重大風險，這些風險包括過度使用自然資源、破壞生態系統和排放污染物。<ref>{{Cite web|title="Greening the Belt and Road Initiative"|url=}}</ref>作為「一带一路」的一部分，中國向外資助了燃煤發電站，例如土耳其的 Emba Hunutlu 發電站，環保組織認為這增加了溫室氣體排放和令全球變暖。<ref>{{Cite web|title=China’s Belt and Road Initiative Could Drive Warming to 2.7 Degrees|url=https://e360.yale.edu/digest/chinas-belt-and-road-initiative-could-drive-warming-to-2-7-degrees|access-date=2022-04-12|work=Yale E360|language=en-US|archive-date=2019-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925175240/https://e360.yale.edu/digest/chinas-belt-and-road-initiative-could-drive-warming-to-2-7-degrees}}</ref>據德國環保組織 Urgewald 稱，中國能源公司將佔預計未來十年並網的新燃煤電廠發電量的近一半。<ref>{{Cite news|title=As Beijing Joins Climate Fight, Chinese Companies Build Coal Plants|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/01/climate/china-energy-companies-coal-plants-climate-change.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2017-07-01|accessdate=2022-04-12|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Hiroko|last=Tabuchi|archive-date=2022-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419045908/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/01/climate/china-energy-companies-coal-plants-climate-change.html}}</ref>數據顯示與「一带一路」絲路基金中的能源投資有 93% 是用於投資化石燃料。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Moving the Green Belt and Road Initiative: From Words to Actions|url=https://www.wri.org/research/moving-green-belt-and-road-initiative-words-actions|last=Zhou|first=Lihuan|last2=Gilbert|first2=Sean|date=2018-08-11|language=en|last3=Wang|first3=Ye|last4=Cabré|first4=Miquel Muñoz|last5=Gallagher|first5=Kevin P.|journal=|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2022-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517165546/https://www.wri.org/research/moving-green-belt-and-road-initiative-words-actions}}</ref>另外，與海上丝绸之路倡議相關的港口基礎設施建設和航運增加，可能會影響敏感物種和海洋棲息地，如珊瑚礁、紅樹林、海草草地和鹽沼等。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=China's Belt and Road Initiative: Conservation opportunities for threatened marine species and habitats|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0308597X19307675|last=Turschwell|first=Mischa P.|last2=Brown|first2=Christopher J.|date=2020-02-01|journal=Marine Policy|doi=10.1016/j.marpol.2019.103791|volume=112|pages=103791|language=en|issn=0308-597X|last3=Pearson|first3=Ryan M.|last4=Connolly|first4=Rod M.}}</ref>

在2017年「一带一路」國際合作高峰論壇開幕式上，中國領導人習近平指出，「一带一路」要「踐行綠色發展新理念，踐行綠色低碳、循環可持續的生活方式和工作方式」。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Full text of President Xi's speech at opening of Belt and Road forum - Xinhua {{!}} English.news.cn|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-05/14/c_136282982.htm|access-date=2022-04-12|work=www.xinhuanet.com|archive-date=2022-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220507110426/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-05/14/c_136282982.htm}}</ref>聯合國開發計劃署和 CCIEE 的報告將「一带一路」倡議視為環境保護的機會，只要它被用於提供可持續發展目標相一致的綠色貿易、金融和投資，將有助世界步入綠色經濟。<ref>{{Cite web|title=A New Means to Transformative Global Governance Towards Sustainable Development {{!}} UNDP in China|url=https://www.cn.undp.org/content/china/en/home/library/south-south-cooperation/a-new-means-to-transformative-global-governance-towards-sustaina.html|access-date=2022-04-12|work=UNDP|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505215832/https://www.cn.undp.org/content/china/en/home/library/south-south-cooperation/a-new-means-to-transformative-global-governance-towards-sustaina.html}}</ref>其他提議包括為旨在履行對《巴黎協定》貢獻的「一带一路」成員國提供財政支持，或提供資源和政策專業知識以幫助成員國擴大可再生能源的占比。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Environmental Governance of China's Belt and Road Initiative|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/eet.1901|last=Coenen|first=Johanna|last2=Bager|first2=Simon|date=2021-01|journal=Environmental Policy and Governance|issue=1|doi=10.1002/eet.1901|volume=31|pages=3–17|language=en|issn=1756-932X|last3=Meyfroidt|first3=Patrick|last4=Newig|first4=Jens|last5=Challies|first5=Edward|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2022-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220426082123/https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/eet.1901}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Potential of Photovoltaics to Power the Belt and Road Initiative|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2542435119302752|last=Chen|first=Shi|last2=Lu|first2=Xi|date=2019-08-21|journal=Joule|issue=8|doi=10.1016/j.joule.2019.06.006|volume=3|pages=1895–1912|language=en|issn=2542-4351|last3=Miao|first3=Yufei|last4=Deng|first4=Yu|last5=Nielsen|first5=Chris P.|last6=Elbot|first6=Noah|last7=Wang|first7=Yuanchen|last8=Logan|first8=Kathryn G.|last9=McElroy|first9=Michael B.|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2022-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425152307/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2542435119302752}}</ref>

