=== 「債務陷阱外交」的指責 ===
{{main|債務陷阱外交}}有人擔心該「一帶一路」項目是一種新殖民主義，包括美國在內的一些政府指責「一帶一路」是[[債務陷阱外交|債務陷阱外交]]，這術語是由印度智庫布拉瑪·切拉尼創造的，<ref name=":02">{{cite news|author=Brahma Chellaney|title=China's Debt-Trap Diplomacy|newspaper=Project Syndicate|date=23 January 2017|url=https://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/china-one-belt-one-road-loans-debt-by-brahma-chellaney-2017-01|accessdate=2022-04-07|archive-date=2017-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129090158/https://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/china-one-belt-one-road-loans-debt-by-brahma-chellaney-2017-01}}</ref>於2017年首次使用，並在一年內就傳遍了媒體、情報界和西方政府。<ref name="Brautigam meme">{{Cite journal|title=A critical look at Chinese 'debt-trap diplomacy': the rise of a meme|last=Brautigam|first=Deborah|date=2 January 2020|journal=Area Development and Policy|issue=1|doi=10.1080/23792949.2019.1689828|volume=5|pages=1–14|issn=2379-2949|s2cid=214547742}}</ref>比如，由美國政府資助的媒體[[美國之音|美國之音]]就批評中國大陸藉「一帶一路」等方式向亞太部分國家提供貸款，進行「債務外交」，指過分借貸會導致國家主權陷入中國的手中，<ref>{{Cite web|title=300多億美元項目被廢！「一帶一路」在亞非中東碰壁|url=https://newtalk.tw/news/view/2018-10-17/153682|access-date=2019-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210703080134/https://newtalk.tw/news/view/2018-10-17/153682|archive-date=2021-07-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>另外也有一些國家也有同樣擔憂。<ref name="ps">{{Cite web|title=China's Debt-Trap Diplomacy|url=https://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/china-one-belt-one-road-loans-debt-by-brahma-chellaney-2017-01?barrier=accesspaylog|access-date=2018-09-15|date=2017-01-23|last=Chellaney|first=Brahma|website=Project Syndicate|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102022604/https://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/china-one-belt-one-road-loans-debt-by-brahma-chellaney-2017-01?barrier=accesspaylog|archive-date=2019-11-02|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.usni.org/2018/10/02/panel-chinese-investments-to-boost-trade-come-as-u-s-commercial-shipping-in-decline|title=Panel: Chinese Investments to Boost Trade Come as U.S. Commercial Shipping in Decline - USNI News|date=2018-10-02|work=USNI News|access-date=2018-10-09|archive-date=2019-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191014025327/https://news.usni.org/2018/10/02/panel-chinese-investments-to-boost-trade-come-as-u-s-commercial-shipping-in-decline|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

一些人士認為，這種做法凸顯了中國的霸權意圖及其對國家主權的挑戰。<ref>{{Cite web|title=China's Era of Debt-Trap Diplomacy May Pave the Way for Something Sinister|url=https://nationalinterest.org/feature/chinas-era-debt-trap-diplomacy-may-pave-way-something-sinister-42927|access-date=2022-04-06|date=2019-02-03|last=Patrick Mendis|first=Joey Wang|work=The National Interest|language=en|archive-date=2019-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401015136/https://nationalinterest.org/feature/chinas-era-debt-trap-diplomacy-may-pave-way-something-sinister-42927}}</ref>2018年8月，一個由16名美國參議員組成的跨黨派團體指中國債務陷阱外交有危險，「美國必須反擊中國企圖將其他國家扣為人質並強制贖金以推進其地緣戰略目標的企圖」。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Grassley, Senators Express Concerns over China’s “Debt Trap” Diplomacy with Developing Countries {{!}} U.S. Senator Chuck Grassley of Iowa|url=https://www.grassley.senate.gov/news/news-releases/grassley-senators-express-concerns-over-china-s-debt-trap-diplomacy-developing/|access-date=2022-04-07|work=www.grassley.senate.gov|language=en|archive-date=2022-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220422064947/https://www.grassley.senate.gov/news/news-releases/grassley-senators-express-concerns-over-china-s-debt-trap-diplomacy-developing/}}</ref>美國國務卿[[邁克·蓬佩奧|邁克·蓬佩奧]]在2018年10月的一次演講中表示，中國的貸款是通過賄賂以提供便利的，他指控「中國向各國高級領導人行賄，以換取基礎設施項目」。<ref>{{Cite web|title=China's massive Belt and Road initiative builds global infrastructure -- and influence|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/how-historic-belt-and-road-infrastructure-project-is-building-chinas-global-influence|access-date=2022-04-07|date=2019-09-27|work=PBS NewsHour|language=en-us|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505074747/https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/how-historic-belt-and-road-infrastructure-project-is-building-chinas-global-influence}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Pompeo says US to fight China 'empire' of 'bribes'|url=http://www.energy-daily.com/reports/Pompeo_says_US_to_fight_China_empire_of_bribes_999.html|access-date=2022-04-07|work=Energy Daily|archive-date=2022-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419050318/https://www.energy-daily.com/reports/Pompeo_says_US_to_fight_China_empire_of_bribes_999.html}}</ref>

印度評論員查特吉（S. K. Chatterji）認為這是中國對領土申索的戰略。<ref name="terri1">{{cite news|first=S. K.|last=Chatterji|url=https://asiatimes.com/2020/10/wider-connotations-of-chinese-salami-slicing/|title=Wider connotations of Chinese 'salami slicing'|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101114831/https://asiatimes.com/2020/10/wider-connotations-of-chinese-salami-slicing/|archive-date=1 November 2020|work=Asia Times|date=22 October 2020}}</ref>查特吉認為中國正利用債務陷阱來淡化目標國家的主權。中國透過大量外借金錢給予與其有領土爭議的國家，借此換取在領土談判上的優勢。<ref>{{Cite news|title=China is thinking twice about lending to Africa|url=https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/06/29/china-is-thinking-twice-about-lending-to-africa|newspaper=The Economist|access-date=12 December 2020|archive-date=18 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218134328/https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/06/29/china-is-thinking-twice-about-lending-to-africa|url-status=live}}</ref>

