lomacy Rhetoric surrounding Hambantota Port|url=https://gjia.georgetown.edu/2021/06/05/questioning-the-debt-trap-diplomacy-rhetoric-surrounding-hambantota-port/|website=Georgetown Journal of International Affairs|accessdate=2022-04-07|archive-date=2021-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210626130227/https://gjia.georgetown.edu/2021/06/05/questioning-the-debt-trap-diplomacy-rhetoric-surrounding-hambantota-port/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Rithmire|first2=Deborah|last2=Brautigam|first1=Meg|date=2021-02-06|title=The Chinese ‘Debt Trap’ Is a Myth|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2021/02/china-debt-trap-diplomacy/617953/|newspaper=The Atlantic|accessdate=2022-04-07|archive-date=2022-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518183623/https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2021/02/china-debt-trap-diplomacy/617953/}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite journal|title=A critical look at Chinese 'debt-trap diplomacy': the rise of a meme|author=Deborah Bräutigam|url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/23792949.2019.1689828?journalCode=rard20|journal=Area Development and Policy|access-date=2022-04-07|archive-date=2021-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221125706/https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/23792949.2019.1689828?journalCode=rard20}}</ref>[[约翰斯·霍普金斯大学|約翰霍普金斯大學]]高級國際研究學院教授黛博拉·布勞蒂加姆 （Deborah Bräutigam） 將債務陷阱外交描述為一種「[[迷因|模因]]（meme）」，是由於對中國快速崛起而引發的焦慮而流行，是「人類消極的偏見」。根據2019年的一篇研究論文顯示，大多數債務國是自願同意接受貸款，並且有與中國合作有過的積極經驗，他指「包括斯里蘭卡的案例在內迄今為止的證據，都誇大了中國銀行融資和一帶一路的風險」。<ref name=":32">{{Cite journal|title=A critical look at Chinese 'debt-trap diplomacy': the rise of a meme|author=Deborah Bräutigam|url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/23792949.2019.1689828?journalCode=rard20|journal=Area Development and Policy|access-date=2022-04-07|archive-date=2021-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221125706/https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/23792949.2019.1689828?journalCode=rard20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=美媒： 指責中國「殖民主義」有誇大 西方應向發展中國家多投資|url=https://www.hk01.com/即時中國/547581/美媒-指責中國-殖民主義-有誇大-西方應向發展中國家多投資|access-date=2022-04-12|date=2020-11-11|last=李亭|work=香港01|language=zh-HK|archive-date=2022-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220412105710/https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B/547581/%E7%BE%8E%E5%AA%92-%E6%8C%87%E8%B2%AC%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B-%E6%AE%96%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%BB%E7%BE%A9-%E6%9C%89%E8%AA%87%E5%A4%A7-%E8%A5%BF%E6%96%B9%E6%87%89%E5%90%91%E7%99%BC%E5%B1%95%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B%E5%AE%B6%E5%A4%9A%E6%8A%95%E8%B3%87}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=U.S. politicians get China in Africa all wrong|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/theworldpost/wp/2018/04/12/china-africa/|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2019-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428070923/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/theworldpost/wp/2018/04/12/china-africa/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=「一帶一路」是債務陷阱外交嗎？|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/opinion/20190429/china-belt-road-initiative/zh-hant/|author=DEBORAH BRAUTIGAM|date=2019年4月29日|publisher=nytimes|access-date=2022年4月12日|archive-date=2020年11月10日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110013741/https://cn.nytimes.com/opinion/20190429/china-belt-road-initiative/zh-hant/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=美媒： 指责中国新殖民主义也许夸张了｜多维新闻｜中国|url=https://www.dwnews.com/中国/60218551/美媒指责中国新殖民主义也许夸张了|access-date=2022-04-14|date=2020-11-11|last=多维新闻|work=多维新闻|language=zh-Hans|archive-date=2021-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210228163233/https://www.dwnews.com/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD/60218551/%E7%BE%8E%E5%AA%92%E6%8C%87%E8%B4%A3%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E6%96%B0%E6%AE%96%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%BB%E4%B9%89%E4%B9%9F%E8%AE%B8%E5%A4%B8%E5%BC%A0%E4%BA%86}}</ref>他批評媒體的宣傳，指他們錯誤地歪曲了中國與其他發展中國家之間的關係。很多發展中國家對中國的經濟模式有好感，並認為中國是對他們來說有吸引力的發展伙伴。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Chinese ‘Debt Trap’ Is a Myth|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2021/02/china-debt-trap-diplomacy/617953/|access-date=2022-04-07|date=2021-02-06|last=Rithmire|first=Deborah Brautigam, Meg|work=The Atlantic|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518183623/https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2021/02/china-debt-trap-diplomacy/617953/}}</ref>由黛博拉合著的2018年中非研究計劃報告指出，中國貸款目前並不是非洲債務困境的主要因素。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Path Ahead: The 7th Forum on China-Africa Cooperation|url=https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5652847de4b033f56d2bdc29/t/5c467754898583fc9a99131f/1548121941093/Briefing+Paper+1+-+August+2018+-+Final.pdf|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2022-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220504200536/https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5652847de4b033f56d2bdc29/t/5c467754898583fc9a99131f/1548121941093/Briefing+Paper+1+-+August+2018+-+Final.pdf}}</ref>

紐約經濟學家阿納斯塔西婭·帕帕迪米特里烏（Anastasia Papadimitriou）指在與中國進行交易時，夥伴國同樣負有責任。<ref name="#7">{{Cite web|title=China's Belt and Road Initiative: Is it Truly Neocolonialist?|url=https://www.theworldmind.org/home/2019/10/20/chinas-belt-and-road-initiative-is-it-truly-neocolonialist|access-date=2022-04-12|work=The World Mind|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220331114406/https://www.theworldmind.org/home/2019/10/20/chinas-belt-and-road-initiative-is-it-truly-neocolonialist}}</ref>另外他在分析「一帶一路」倡議後，阿納斯塔西婭得出結論，說︰「與其說是新殖民主義，倒不如說是經濟區域主義」。<ref name="#7"/>洛伊國際政策研究所在2019年發表的一份報告指出，[[斯里蘭卡|斯里蘭卡]][[漢班托塔港|漢班托塔港]]案例是西方宣傳中國債務陷阱外交的「傑出案例（case par excellence）」，但現實情況卻只是一個「錯誤的觀念（myth）」。中國曾貸款給斯里蘭卡興建[[漢班托塔港|漢班托塔港]]，但由於斯里蘭卡無法償還債務，該港口和附近15000英畝土地被交由中國[[招商局集團|招商局]]港口公司，租期99年，此舉被西方媒體批評為債務陷阱外交。當時已有斯里蘭卡官員反駁此一說法，說︰「如果是中國強行要給我們貸款，那你可以說成是陷阱，但我們向中國貸的每分錢，都是我們自己要求的」。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sri Lanka rejects fears of China’s ‘debt-trap diplomacy’|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3007175/sri-lanka-rejects-fears-chinas-debt-trap-diplomacy-belt-and|access-date=2022-04-07|date=2019-04-22|work=South China Morning Post|language=en|archive-date=2022-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220407012057/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3007175/sri-lanka-rejects-fears-chinas-debt-trap-diplomacy-belt-and}}</ref>洛伊國際政策研究所指出港口是斯里蘭卡前總理[[马欣达·拉贾帕克萨|馬欣達·拉賈帕克薩]]要求興建的，中國只是給予了貸款支持，並沒有參與到決策中。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Debunking the myth of China’s “debt-trap diplomacy”|url=https://www.lowyinstitute.org/the-interpreter/debunking-myth-china-s-debt-trap-diplomacy|access-date=2022-04-07|work=www.lowyinstitute.org|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505045022/https://www.lowyinstitute.org/the-interpreter/debunking-myth-china-s-debt-trap-diplomacy}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Experts dispel claims of China debt-trap diplomacy in Pacific but risks remain|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/oct/21/chinese-loans-expose-pacific-islands-to-risk-of-unsustainable-debt-report-finds|access-date=2022-04-07|date=2019-10-20|work=the Guardian|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517000006/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/oct/21/chinese-loans-expose-pacific-islands-to-risk-of-unsustainable-debt-report-finds}}</ref> 此外，英國智庫[[漆咸樓|皇家國際事務研究所]]同樣質疑「債務陷阱」的說法，指該港口的交易是由當地政治動機驅動的，而且中國從未正式擁有該港口。斯里蘭卡的債務危機與中國的貸款無關，而是主要由「當地精英的不當行為和西方主導的金融市場」導致的，而且沒有證據表明中國利用其地位從港口獲得戰略軍事優勢。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Debunking the Myth of ‘Debt-trap Diplomacy’|url=https://www.chathamhouse.org/2020/08/debunking-myth-debt-trap-diplomacy|access-date=2022-04-12|date=2020-08-19|work=Chatham House – International Affairs Think Tank|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505054610/https://www.chathamhouse.org/2020/08/debunking-myth-debt-trap-diplomacy}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Opinion {{!}} Is China the World’s Loan Shark?|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/26/opinion/china-belt-road-initiative.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2019-04-26|accessdate=2022-04-16|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Deborah|last=Brautigam|archive-date=2019-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430151136/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/26/opinion/china-belt-road-initiative.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=China: Is it burdening poor countries with unsustainable debt?|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/59585507|newspaper=BBC News|date=2022-01-06|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512093309/https://www.bbc.com/news/59585507}}</ref>

位於紐約的研究中心Rhodium Group也指出，中國在債務重新談判上的影響力經常被誇大，他實際上的權力有限。研究顯示談判的有利方通常都是借款人而不是所謂的掠奪性的中國貸方。<ref>{{Cite web|title=New Data on the "Debt Trap" Question|url=https://rhg.com/research/new-data-on-the-debt-trap-question/|access-date=2022-04-07|work=Rhodium Group|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505090450/https://rhg.com/research/new-data-on-the-debt-trap-question/}}</ref>

[[澳大利亞國立大學|澳大利亞國立大學]]高級講師達倫·林 （Darren Lim） 表示，「債務陷阱外交」的說法從不可信，儘管特朗普政府大力推動了這一說法。<ref name="#8">{{Cite web|title=Data doesn't support Belt and Road debt trap claims|url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/asia/data-doesn-t-support-belt-and-road-debt-trap-claims-20190502-p51jhx.html|access-date=2022-04-12|date=2019-05-02|last=Needham|first=Kirsty|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505090852/https://www.smh.com.au/world/asia/data-doesn-t-support-belt-and-road-debt-trap-claims-20190502-p51jhx.html}}</ref>

政治學家及研究員張哲新認為，2017年5月舉行的「一帶一路」國際合作高峰論壇上，發展中國家對「一帶一路」倡議展現壓倒性的熱情，這已足以使新殖民主義的指控失效。<ref name="#9">{{Cite journal|title=The Belt and Road Initiative: China’s New Geopolitical Strategy?|url=https://www.worldscientific.com/doi/abs/10.1142/S2377740018500240|last=Zhang|first=Zhexin|date=2018-01-01|journal=China Quarterly of International Strategic Studies|issue=03|doi=10.1142/S2377740018500240|volume=04|pages=327–343|issn=2377-7400|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2021-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211217221200/https://www.worldscientific.com/doi/abs/10.1142/S2377740018500240}}</ref>

全球發展中心在2018年3月發布的一份報告稱，在2001年至2017年期間，中國重組或免除了51個債務國的貸款，大多數是一帶一路參與國，而且沒有沒收他們的國有資產。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Examining the Debt Implications of the Belt and Road Initiative from a Policy Perspective|author=Hurley, John; Morris, Scott; Portelance, Gailyn|url=https://www.cgdev.org/sites/default/files/examining-debt-implications-belt-and-road-initiative-policy-perspective.pdf|journal=Center for Global Development|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505130731/https://www.cgdev.org/sites/default/files/examining-debt-implications-belt-and-road-initiative-policy-perspective.pdf}}</ref>[[利比里亚|利比里亞]]前公共工程部長、全球發展中心高級政策研究員摩爾（W. Gyude Moore）表示，「債務陷阱外交」等政治化語言在西方國家，尤其是在美國引起了很大的回響，並且是根深蒂固的概念。他們是在擔心中國崛起會成為全球大國，而不是擔心非洲的現實。這些是西方自己的焦慮，而不是非洲國家的焦慮。他還補充說：「中國一直是大多數非洲國家的積極合作夥伴。」<ref>{{Cite web|title=The language of "debt-trap diplomacy" reflects Western anxieties, not African realities|url=https://qz.com/1391770/the-anxious-chorus-around-chinese-debt-trap-diplomacy-doesnt-reflect-african-realities/|access-date=2022-04-07|last=Moore|first=W. Gyude|work=Quartz|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505123221/https://qz.com/1391770/the-anxious-chorus-around-chinese-debt-trap-diplomacy-doesnt-reflect-african-realities/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=美國沿「一帶一路」鼓勵各國對中國說「不」|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese-news-45969055|newspaper=BBC News 中文|accessdate=2022-04-14|language=zh-hant|quote=利比里亞前公共工程部長摩爾（W. Gyude Moore）用實例反駁了中國推行"債務外交"的說法。他認為西方，特別是美國特別喜歡用"債務外交"批評中國，這反映出他們對中國全球影響力擴大的焦慮。摩爾在美國財經網站Quartz發表文章說，在過去15年中的84個案例說明中國的貸款重組或放棄並沒有導致中國取得當地的資產。即使在通常被援引的委內瑞拉案例中，中國並沒有在那裏獲取該國主要的國有資產。|archive-date=2022-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220407011214/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese-news-45969055}}</ref>

[[南洋理工大学|新加坡南洋理工大學]]的普拉杜納·比克拉姆·拉娜（Pradumna Bickram Rana）及嵇先白表示，儘管「一帶一路」倡議面臨許多實施問題，但這主要是由於 COVID-19的大流行，所謂的債務陷阱外交的講法是不可信的。<ref name="#9"/>雖然他們承認各國在償還中國債務方面面臨困難，但他們強調中國願意通過部分債務減免等寬恕政策幫助這些國家重組債務。<ref>{{Cite web|title=China Offers Debt Relief, But Most African Countries Borrow Elsewhere|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/china-offers-debt-relief-but-most-african-countries-borrow-elsewhere/4560319.html|access-date=2022-04-12|work=VOA|language=en|archive-date=2018-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181220232537/https://www.voanews.com/a/china-offers-debt-relief-but-most-african-countries-borrow-elsewhere/4560319.html}}</ref>在11個償還困難的案例中，中國推遲了對負債國家的貸款，其中一個例子是湯加。<ref name="#8"/>

==== 另外的批評和意見 ====
與[[國際貨幣基金組織|國際貨幣基金組織、]][[世界银行|世界銀行]]和[[巴黎俱樂部|巴黎俱樂部]]等機構相比，中國的貸款被認為是更快、更便宜，而且附帶的條件也更少。但也遭到尤其是來自美國的高度批評，認為這種「無條件貸款（No-strings loans）」最後只會讓腐敗的當地政府受利。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Reality Check: Is China burdening Africa with debt?|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-45916060|newspaper=BBC News|date=2018-11-05|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|quote=Compared to institutions such as the IMF, World Bank and Paris Club (a group of 22 creditor nations not including China), loans from China are seen by some as much quicker, cheaper, and come with fewer strings attached.The United States in particular has been highly critical of China's approach.|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505115259/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-45916060}}</ref>另外也有批評者指責中國的貸款讓一些國家借此避免了改革，避開了傳統西方捐助者的審查。<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's secret aid empire uncovered|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841|newspaper=BBC News|date=2017-10-11|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427045131/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841}}</ref>不過也有人認為這是件好事，因為非洲國家及其他窮國將有有更多的選擇。<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's secret aid empire uncovered|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841|newspaper=BBC News|date=2017-10-11|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|quote=Traditional donors have criticised China's approach to aid," he says, but "many African countries embrace the assistance from Beijing, or at least are glad to have more options".|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427045131/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841}}</ref>經濟學家迪亞哥·赫南德茲指出，中國作為世界新主要貸款人的角色促進了與傳統捐助者之間的競爭，也迫使傳統捐助者停止對接受國提出許多的要求。<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's secret aid empire uncovered|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841|newspaper=BBC News|date=2017-10-11|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|quote=There is evidence that China's no-strings loans have had an effect on the entire global lending system, forcing traditional donors to stop placing so many requirements on receiving countries. Using AidData's database, economist Diego Hernandez revealed that China's role as a major lender has boosted competition between traditional donors.|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427045131/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841}}</ref>他發現，中國的援助每增加1%，世界銀行就會將其對市場自由化或經濟透明度等方面的典型要求降低15%。<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's secret aid empire uncovered|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841|newspaper=BBC News|date=2017-10-11|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|quote="When an African country is also assisted by China," he writes, "the World Bank provides fewer conditions attached to its loans". For every 1% increase in Chinese aid, Hernandez found the World Bank lessened its typical demands for things like market liberalisation or economic transparency by 15%.|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427045131/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841}}</ref>

另外有聲音認為，即使中國沒有真的在實行債務陷阱外交，但這種大規模的貸款也存在無法持續的隱憂。美國的AidData研究中心指，1960年代至1990年代，西方國家也曾向發展中國家提供大規模的貸款，然而，當受援國無法開始償還債務時，該戰略就失敗了，民眾的憤怒接踵而至，西方的援助模式因此被徹底改革。AidData研究中心說，到目前為止，數據顯示這種情況雖然並沒有出現，但研究人員擔心這種情況可能會在10或15年內發生變化，屆時中國可能不得不重新考慮其貸款型式的可持續性。<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's secret aid empire uncovered|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841|newspaper=BBC News|date=2017-10-11|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|quote=In the 1960s to the 1990s, Western countries offered high-interest market-rate loans to developing countries. However, that strategy misfired when recipient countries could not begin to repay the interest on the debts they had acquired. Outrage ensued and the Western aid model was overhauled.So far, the data shows that the countries that receive China's market-rate loans are not suffering economically, but they aren't experiencing economic growth either. Researchers fear that could change in 10 or 15 years, when countries build up debts because they can't repay the money they will owe to Beijing. At that point, China might have to rethink things.|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427045131/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-41564841}}</ref>

利比里亞前公共工程部長居德·摩爾表示，中國其實就像任何其他貸方一樣，並表示是否接受中國貸款最終是取決於非洲國家自己。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Reality Check: Is China burdening Africa with debt?|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-45916060|newspaper=BBC News|date=2018-11-05|accessdate=2022-04-16|language=en-GB|quote="China is just like any other lender and ultimately, it is up to African nations themselves to accept or reject Chinese loans." says Gyude Moore, a former Liberian Government official.|archive-date=2022-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505115259/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-45916060}}</ref>

貝爾弗科學與國際事務中心2018年發表的一篇論文提出中國大量貸款背後的三個戰略目標：（1）解決其[[珍珠链战略|珍珠鏈戰略]]困境；（2）在重要的南亞貿易路線上投射力量；（3）破壞以美國為首的地區聯盟對中國的包圍，使[[中国人民解放军海军|中國人民解放軍海軍]]能夠突破「[[第二岛链|第二島鏈]]」。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Debtbook Diplomacy|author=Sam Parker; Gabrielle Chefitz|url=https://www.belfercenter.org/sites/default/files/files/publication/Debtbook%20Diplomacy%20PDF.pdf|journal=Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs|access-date=2022-04-19|archive-date=2022-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220506153930/https://www.belfercenter.org/sites/default/files/files/publication/Debtbook%20Diplomacy%20PDF.pdf}}</ref>

== 「一帶一路」教育社區 ==
「一帶一路」的其中一個主要目標是加強教育交流，意味著學歷互認、學術流動和學生交流、教育政策協調、終身學習和聯合學習項目的發展。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Constructing a Eurasian higher education region: “Points of correspondence” between Russia’s Eurasian Economic Union and China’s Belt and Road Initiative in Central Asia|url=https://doi.org/10.1080/15387216.2020.1866997|last=Leskina|first=Natalia|last2=Sabzalieva|first2=Emma|date=2021-11-02|journal=Eurasian Geography and Economics|issue=5-6|doi=10.1080/15387216.2020.1866997|volume=62|pages=716–744|issn=1538-7216}}</ref>為此，習近平在2013年宣布計劃再撥款30000名上合組織公民獎學金和10000名「一帶一路」沿線師生獎學金名額。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Xi proposes a 'new Silk Road' with Central Asia[1]|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2013xivisitcenterasia/2013-09/08/content_16952228.htm|date=2013-09-08|access-date=2022-04-12|work=www.chinadaily.com.cn|archive-date=2022-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220331114402/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2013xivisitcenterasia/2013-09/08/content_16952228.htm}}</ref>以[[西安交通大學|西安交通大學]]為中心的絲綢之路高校聯盟旨在通過研究和工程支持「一帶一路」倡議，促進理解和學術交流。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Belt and Road Initiative|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Belt_and_Road_Initiative&oldid=1082283841|date=2022-04-12|journal=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2022-04-12|archive-date=2022-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419050654/https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Belt_and_Road_Initiative&oldid=1082283841}}</ref>

